page.title: 11Animal Deaths on the A.35.
page.content: The main road,{A.35,}is fenced to prevent wild animals from straying.However,the height of this does not prevent{deer}from jumping over.The {Forest Keeper,}whom we spoke to, had to date dealt with approximately four animal deaths.The months March and April are the times when there is the highest number of deer deaths due to the mating season.The Forest Keeper officially only has jurisdiction within the Forest boundaries.However,he does have occasion to deal with deaths on other parts of the A.35,namely that part of the road which runs through the Meyrick Estates.
